CSS Syntax Exercise

X Download this skeleton. 

X Add a new external stylesheet to the assets folder, and add a link tag for it in the html page. 

X Open up the html page in your web browser and use the CSS workflow from Day 1 to begin styling the recipe page with some basic CSS syntax.


X Select the body element and set the font-family property to "Arial, sans-serif"

X Set the font-size to 38px for all H1 elements

X Set the font-size to 32px for all H2 elements

X Add a class to your unordered list of ingredients called "ingredients-list"

X Add a list-style property with a value of "square inside" to all elements with the "ingredients-list" class

X Add another list-style of your choosing to all ordered list elements

X Change the width of the logo image to 100px by selecting all img elements that are immediate children of the header element


Hint: Use >

X Select all anchor elements within list elements within unordered list elements and remove their underlines. Also change their color to inherit.

X Give your whole recipe page a nice background-color

X Set the line-height to 1.5 in your css_reset file


Challenge: Come up with a way to select and style your reviews after they are submitted. For now just some simple font-styling is fine.

When you review the solution, carefully review the stylesheet and compare to your own.